Assignment

About Closira
Closira is an AI-powered customer communication platform built for small and medium
businesses (SMBs). It handles inbound customer enquiries across WhatsApp, email, and
phone, responding using business-defined SOPs (Standard Operating Procedures) to respond
accurately, qualify leads, schedule follow-ups, and escalate to human agents when required.
As an AI Engineering Intern, you will be building the intelligence layer that powers these
conversations, designing prompts, building agentic workflows, and ensuring the AI behaves
safely and reliably in real customer interactions.
Objective
Build a simple AI-powered customer support workflow that demonstrates your ability to design
prompts, structure multi-step AI logic, and ensure the system behaves safely and escalates
when it should.
Assignment
What you will build
A Python-based AI workflow using the OpenAI or Anthropic Claude API that handles a
simulated customer conversation end-to-end across four stages:
# Stage What it does
1 FAQ Answering Answer inbound customer questions using a provided SOP data file
(JSON or plain text). Respond only from the SOP; do not hallucinate
facts not present in it.

2 Lead
Qualification

Ask the customer 2–3 structured questions to qualify them (e.g.,
business type, team size, current tools). Collect and store responses.

3 Escalation
Detection

Detect when the AI should hand off to a human: low confidence,
out-of-scope question, angry sentiment, or explicit escalation request.
Flag and log the reason.

4 Conversation
Summary

At the end of a session, generate a structured summary: customer
intent, key details collected, SOP gaps identified, and recommended
next action.

SOP Data
Use the following as your SOP source (or create your own for a fictional SMB). Your AI must
answer from this data only:

Sample SOP — Closira Demo Business
Business: Bloom Aesthetics Clinic
Hours: Mon–Sat, 9 am–7 pm
Services: Botox (from £200), Fillers (from £250), Consultations (free)
Booking: Via WhatsApp or website. 24hr cancellation required.
Escalate if: complaint, medical question, pricing negotiation, or > 2
unanswered questions.
You may extend or replace this SOP with your own. Clearly document what data your AI
operates on.

Prompt Design Requirements
You must submit a prompt_design.md file alongside your code covering:
● System prompt: Your full system prompt for the AI, with reasoning for key design
choices
● Hallucination prevention: How you instruct the model to stay within SOP boundaries
and avoid making up information
● Confidence-based escalation: How you detect when the AI is uncertain and should
hand off (e.g., explicit flag, threshold, output format)
● Tone and persona: How you define the AI's communication style for an SMB context
Expected AI Behaviours
Your workflow must handle these scenarios correctly. Include test transcripts in your submission
for each:
1. In-SOP question: Customer asks, "What are your Botox prices?"
AI answers accurately from SOP only
2. Out-of-scope question: Customer asks something not in the SOP.
AI acknowledges the gap and escalates rather than guessing
3. Escalation trigger: Customer expresses frustration or a complaint
AI detects sentiment and hands off with a reason
4. Lead qualification: AI asks structured questions and produces a qualification summary
5. Conversation summary: At session end, AI produces a clean, structured summary with
intent, details, and next action

